# PROMPTS.md

When the user asks to **update**, **append to**, or **log prompts in** `PROMPTS.md`, add their message(s) as new numbered `### N` entries under **Historical prompts** in `PROMPTS.md` (continue numbering from the highest existing prompt), preserving exact wording.

Do not append on every reply by default—only when they ask, or when they use phrases like “log this prompt” / “add to prompts file.”

For “automatic every prompt”: Cursor has no native auto-append; see the “How to maintain” section in `PROMPTS.md`.
